<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,395,890]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,395,422]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wing length 
<quantity box="[423,525,395,423]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="1.65">1.65 mm</quantity>
. Fronto-orbital yellowish; face yellow; pedicel yellowish; legs completely brown; calypter whitish, fringe brownish. Aedeagus (Fig. 9 and 10): basiphallus slightly sclerotized, with a long extension distally; mesophallus enlarged basally; distiphallus forming two short tubules covered by a pair of plates.
</paragraph>
