<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="160" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,395,890]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,719,746]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Stegmaier, C. E. Jr." box="[346,678,720,746]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" pagination="1 - 205" refId="ref21188" refString="Spencer, K. A. &amp; Stegmaier, C. E. Jr. (1973) Agromyzidae of Florida with supplement on species from the Caribbean. Arthropods of Florida and neighboring land areas, 7, 1 - 205." type="journal article" year="1973">Spencer &amp; Stegmaier (1973)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName box="[862,1145,720,746]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahamarum">
<emphasis box="[862,1145,720,746]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">Calycomyza bahamarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a leaf-miner of plants in the family 
<taxonomicName box="[308,449,756,782]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Verbenaceae</taxonomicName>
due to the similarity of its male genitalia with those of three other leaf miner species restricted to this plant family, namely: 
<emphasis box="[594,715,792,819]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">C. durante</emphasis>
Spencer, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Frick)" authorityName="Frick" baseAuthorityName="Frick" box="[829,1051,792,819]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lantanae">
<emphasis box="[829,961,792,819]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">C. lantanae</emphasis>
(Frick)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hering)" authorityName="Hering" baseAuthorityName="Hering" box="[1112,1358,792,819]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verbenae">
<emphasis box="[1112,1250,792,819]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">C. verbenae</emphasis>
(Hering)
</taxonomicName>
. In the present study, 
<taxonomicName box="[309,476,828,855]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahamarum">
<emphasis box="[309,476,828,855]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">C. bahamarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed to 
<taxonomicName box="[665,792,828,854]" form="mines" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" rank="form">form mines</taxonomicName>
on leaves of 
<emphasis box="[936,1254,828,854]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">
<taxonomicName box="[936,1249,828,854]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cayennensis">Stachytarpheta cayennensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
thus confirming its association with the 
<taxonomicName box="[414,555,864,890]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Verbenaceae</taxonomicName>
family.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
